PrecisAmendments (SCHEDULE NO. 992) to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS which provide for the use of the lipase enzyme derived from Rhizopus niveus in the hydrolysis or modification of triglycerides (fats and oils), and correct an inconsistency in Table V to Division 16 with respect to the enzyme chymosin.

precis:
Amendments (SCHEDULE NO. 992) to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS which
provide for the use of the lipase enzyme derived from Rhizopus niveus in
the hydrolysis or modification of triglycerides (fats and oils), and
correct an inconsistency in Table V to Division 16 with respect to the
enzyme chymosin.
